description: Repo-wide Rowset steering files and AI agent guardrails
alwaysApply: true
---

- Read `AGENTS.md` for commands, workflow, guardrails, and code style.
- Use `PRODUCT.md`, `TECH.md`, `STRUCTURE.md`, `VISION.md`, and `DESIGN.md` for product, stack, repo layout, long-term direction, and UI context.
- Use `docs/quality.md` for the local CI path and touched-area quality matrix.
- Keep dataset, REST API, and MCP behavior aligned through shared services.
- Prefer `make test ...` over host `pytest`.
- Never hand-write migrations; use `make makemigrations`.
- Keep API keys, OAuth tokens, service-account JSON, and private dataset contents out of generated code, docs, logs, and responses.
